        <p>American editor and writer. Head of a Baltimore girls’ school, 1868–72. Writer and associate editor, <hi rend="italic">Southern Review</hi>, 1872–77; editor, 1877. Studied biology at Johns Hopkins University in 1876. An editor of <hi rend="italic">Scribner’s Monthly</hi> from 1879, and its successor, <hi rend="italic">Century</hi>, until 1906. Wrote science books for children, mostly on botany and geology.</p></note>
